# Aero Engine — LeakSanitizer suppressions (task 0.4.2, spec D16: evidence-gated, never pre-seeded).
#
# Scope: wired ONLY into the Debug ctest step's LSAN_OPTIONS for Linux (.github/workflows/ci.yml) —
# the one lane where LSan runs. First-party leak detection stays fully ON: every entry below names a
# specific THIRD-PARTY allocation origin observed on the first GPU-backed CI run (PR #16, run
# 29599267631). There, doctest reported 227/227 SUCCESS and LSan then flagged ~3.1 MB in 57,584
# allocations, all rooted in SDL3's x11 video-driver init and SDL_GPU's Vulkan probe
# (lavapipe/loader frames) — zero allocation sites in engine/ or tests/ code; engine frames appear
# only as mid-stack call sites (Context::Context -> SDL_Init, Device::create ->
# SDL_CreateGPUDeviceWithProperties). Surfaced now because 0.4.2's gated tests are the first thing
# on this lane to init a REAL video driver (x11 under Xvfb); the pre-0.4.2 suite was dummy-driver
# only and never touched these paths.
#
# Rules for this file (spec D16): add an entry ONLY with observed CI evidence, one commented entry
# per observed frame; never suppress module-wide (e.g. leak:SDL) — that would blind LSan to real
# engine leaks whose allocations happen inside SDL (a forgotten SDL_ReleaseGPU* would allocate
# under SDL_CreateGPUBuffer et al., which stay unsuppressed).

# SDL3's x11 video driver retains keyboard/XKB tables per init cycle (SDL_x11keyboard.c:166/:177).
leak:X11_InitKeyboard
# SDL3's x11 video init retains XRandR mode / content-scale data (SDL_x11modes.c, reached from
# X11_VideoInit, SDL_x11video.c:448 — this entry covers those stacks via any-frame matching).
leak:X11_VideoInit
# SDL_GPU's Vulkan backend probe retains loader/lavapipe allocations from instance/physical-device
# enumeration (SDL_gpu_vulkan.c:12362/:12709), reached via both VULKAN_PrepareDriver and
# VULKAN_CreateDevice.
leak:VULKAN_INTERNAL_DeterminePhysicalDevice
leak:VULKAN_INTERNAL_PrepareVulkan
